    "strategy_description": "Heterologous 8-step pathway from L-phenylalanine to 3'-hydroxygenistein via phenylpropanoid, flavonoid, isoflavonoid biosynthesis, and 3'-hydroxylation. Eight plant/fungal enzymes are required (PAL, C4H, 4CL, CHS from A. thaliana; CHI from M. sativa; IFS, HIDH from G. max; CYP57B3 from A. oryzae). Three CYP450 steps (C4H, IFS, CYP57B3) utilize the native yeast NADPH-cytochrome P450 reductase NCP1 (YHR042W). Engineering strategy includes ARO10 knockout to block phenylpyruvate degradation, and overexpression of ARO7 (feedback-resistant mutant), ZWF1, ACS2, and ACC1 to boost precursor and cofactor supply. FBA theoretical maximum flux is 0.667 mmol/gDW/h at zero growth and 0.666 at 10% minimum biomass. Production envelope shows linear growth-production tradeoff. Aerobic conditions required for three O2-dependent CYP450 reactions."
  }
